HEADWORD: Matronal
<hw>Mat"ron*al</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>matronalis</ets>.]</ety> <def>Of or pertaining to a matron;
suitable to an elderly lady or to a married woman; grave;
motherly.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

